title: What era is Victorian housing? - Quora

response.answer_text: Well, let’s see. It’s called Victorian. Is it remotely possible that anyone of passing intelligence might find a clue from that? Wait!!! Yes, one could find out the reign of Queen Victoria by a SIMPLE GOOGLE SEARCH. Look, we all know you’re trying to earn a living by asking questions that are easily answered. Do us all a favor - find a real job.

Loosely speaking, second half of the 19th century. Queen Victoria actually reigned from 1837 to 1901, but buildings in the first few years of her reign are usually regarded as a holdover from the previous Adelaide style.
